RACE.RACE_TEXT: LOUISIANA DOWNS RACE 2 5F Dirt CR: 40. Maiden Claiming Purse 12000. FOR ACCREDITED LA BRED MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DON'T LOOK ETHEL was off mid pack ,l raced two wide, saved ground, stalked down the rail, split horses at the sixteenth pole, shifted into the rail and got up in time for the win. LONG SHOT LOUISE stalked the pace from the three path, raced in between foes, battled down the stretch and the last sixteenth, edged out competitor by a nose for second. E R'S MIREYA vied for the lead, stalked from the five path, nearly took the lead in the furlong ground, inside rival passed on the rail, battled with a rival next to her for second, but just missed running third. TENSAS CLEAR raced from off of the pace, raced on the rail, launched a bid at the seven sixteenth pole, edged out into the four path, shifted into the eight path at the quarter pole, raced in the eight path down the stretch, closed willingly, but was not enough today. SHARE THE DOE vied for the lead, raced on the rail, set the early fractions then faded around the eighth pole. SPARKLE CITY showed little. CALCITE flashed early speed, then settled into mid pack in the four path, loomed up through the turn then flattened out. DON'T BLINK TWICE trailed through out.
